VIRGINIA ELECTRIC AND POWER COMPANY RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 134
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Virginia Electric and Power Company ("Dominion Virginia Power") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from various generating facilities to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") system. This Rate Schedule sets forth Dominion Virginia Power's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM open access transmission tariff. Dominion Virginia Power's monthly revenue requirement is stated below. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
Total Annual Revenue Requirement is $27,500,000. Total Monthly Revenue Requirement is $27,500,000 / 12 = $2,291,667.

VIRGINIA ELECTRIC AND POWER COMPANY
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 135
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Virginia Electric and Power Company d/b/a Dominion Energy/North Carolina ("VEPCO") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from its Virginia City Hybrid Energy Center facility to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") system. This Rate Schedule sets forth VEPCO's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM open access transmission tariff.
VEPCO's annual and monthly revenue requirement is set forth below. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
ANNUAL AND MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $2,950,000 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $2,950,000/ 12 = $245,833.33
